                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some possible responses:
<br />
"Will teir-5 focus effects be equivilent to teir-4 focus effects in rariity and effects as they where when PoP came out?"
<br />

<br />
"If you are doing this so previous content, like time, won't be trivial, why are you making the focus effects in time barely more powerful, and often weaker, than mage summoned foci?  Why should we be bagging our hard-earned elemental bracers for a summoned mage bracer?"
<br />

<br />
"Melee effects, such as vengence, avoidance, crits, dodge, accuracy, strikethrough, combat effects, weapon damage, haste: none of these are less effective when a L 70 player swings their sword.  So melees will gain the benefit of gearing up through VT to Elementals to Time to GoD.  Casters meanwhlie will get meaningless focus effects.  When melee effects cap out (haste, vengence) you add more and different melee effects.  When caster effects cap out, you make old effects obsolete and clone them.  Please add more types of caster focus effects if the existing ones cannot be made to scale."
<br />

<br />
"Your arguement would be accurate if the new common focus effects had the same features as the old hard to get focus effects, ie are L 65 cap and become half effective at L 70.  However, if the new common focus effects are fully funciontal up to L 70 then  what you have done is make previous expansion caster gear obsolete, even as people are progressing through it.  If the content your guild is raiding provides no caster focus upgrades, it doesn't matter if you are in the top of the line guild or someone who finally killed AHR last week, your itemization is screwed.  Please don't screw the itemization of non-bleeding edge guilds."
<br />

<br />
"I have noted that you have missed something that trivializes old content.  HPs and AC.  Because massinve increases in HPs and AC make old content trivial, in order to provide progression while not having HP and AC spiral out of control, old gear will now function less well against higher level monsters.  A piece of "L 65 max" gear will function as if it has 50% of the AC and 50% of the HPs when used agaisnt L 70 intended content.  This will provide an incentive for tanks to gear up in the new expansion without creating power spirals: the added mitigatoin from gainging 5 levels, together with expanding hp/ac on gear, would cause game balance to spiral out of control."</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
