                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, time to be more constructive.
<br />

<br />
The problem is there is a baseline focus effect level.  The "common focus effect".
<br />

<br />
High end, difficult to get gear should not end up decaying below the "common focus effect" level.
<br />

<br />
For improved damage, that is 20%.
<br />

<br />
Instead of having a 50% damage focus drop to 25%, have the difference between your focus effect and the common focus effect level scale.
<br />

<br />
So, 50% is 30% over "common focus effect" level.  That can be cut by 1/2 to 15%, and you end up with a 35% focus at L 70.
<br />

<br />
This is important because take your 30% focus effect from a lower teir raid.
<br />

<br />
Under the SOE sytem, it becomes 15% on L 70 spells.  This is worse than the mage summoned bracer.
<br />

<br />
However, if you use 20% as a baseline, the 30% focus effect becomes 25%.  It is now better than bazaar loot, if by less than it was before.
<br />

<br />
Simular values can be calculated for mana pres, haste, etc.
<br />

<br />
Base haste: 15%
<br />
Base MP: 10%
<br />
Base +Heal: 20%
<br />
Base +Damage: 20%
<br />
Base +Buff Duration: 15%
<br />
Base +Duration Detrimental: 5% (only +Duration are NO DROP)
<br />
Base +Duration Shortbuffs: 5% (ditto)
<br />

<br />
etc.
<br />

<br />
Scale the difference between your focus effect and the base.  Don't scale the focus effect, that penalizes lower end raid focus effects overly harshly.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
