                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, item decay is what we are talking about. Gear that doesn't break but you outgrow it and it does less for you over time.  The thing is, its focused so heavily at levels 65 to 70.  That is the level range that will be hit the hardest with this new plan. 
<br />

<br />
From what SOE seems to be saying the other focus items will have more benefit than before (ie focus levels 1-3), but all endgame items since the release of PoP will only have a 5 level life (since they are level 65 required and 70 is the upper cap). So, the "10 levels of decay" is really pure crap to anyone who is level 65 and planning to go to level 70.
<br />

<br />
If we do find that our level 65 spells (with focus 4 effects) are more efficient than the level 70 spells from OoW (without level 5 focus) then we are still more powerful at 65 than level 70, and the extra levels bought us only HP's and a bit more mana. 
<br />

<br />
So, is that worth paying for? To my mind, I just reversed my decision to buy OoW.  I thought I would like this expansion for what it offers, but really maybe I can make due for 6 months until I see how the drop rate is for Focus5 items. Not just in the drop rate, but the complete re-equipping of all casters in your guild or alliance.  Thats a long F'ing haul just to get the same percentage value focus items we have today.
<br />

<br />
EQ is now officially borked. They can no longer add to the game, without taking away what they gave before.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
